Description : Cathepsin S preproprotein [Rattus norvegicus].
Organism : Rattus norvegicus
Accession Number : NP_059016.2

The Rattus norvegicus, also known as Norway rat, serves as a valuable laboratory model organism.
This is because, it shares genetic similarities with humans and hence, used mostly in research on various human diseases, aging, and cardiovascular conditions.
They are involved in transmitting several zoonotic pathogens to humans, such as helminth parasites.
